Dragon Cult Session Clock - GM Reference
Core Mechanics
Clock Start: Session #1 (when the Great Awakening occurs during "Blood on the Pine")
Advancement: The clock advances to the next Tier at the end of the specified session number
Heroic Intervention: Killing a Dragon Priest postpones the next clock advancement by 2 full sessions
GM Principle: Players are NEVER told about the clock directly. They only experience its consequences through rumors, environmental changes, NPC behavior, and economic shifts.

The Trigger Event: The Sundering Roar
When: During Session #1, while the party is deep within the Sanguine Sanctum in Falkreath
Read Aloud:
"The air in the tomb suddenly becomes heavy, thick with a pressure that makes your ears pop. For a single, heart-stopping moment, all sound vanishesΓÇöthe drip of water, the scuff of your boots, your own breathingΓÇöall swallowed by an absolute and terrifying silence. Then, it hits you. Not a sound you hear with your ears, but one you feel in your soul: a deep, tearing, grinding roar that seems to come from everywhere at once. It is the sound of something ancient and impossibly vast breaking free. The very stones of the crypt hum with the vibration, and a wave of pure, primal dread washes over you, cold and absolute. Then, as quickly as it began, it is over. The silence that follows is more unnerving than the roar itself."
What Actually Happened: Alduin tore through the veil of time at the Throat of the World. He flew to Kynesgrove, resurrected Sahloknir with "SLEN TIID VO!", and massacred the town. This Shout simultaneously awakened all Dragon Priests and their Draugr armies across Skyrim.

Phase 1: The Tremor (Sessions 1-8)
SESSION 1: TIER 0 - THE GREAT AWAKENING
Dragon Cult Action:
Alduin's return triggers simultaneous awakening of all Dragon Priests
Draugr armies begin securing their home tombs
Dragon Priests assess the modern world from their crypts
World State When Party Emerges:
Atmosphere: Panic in Falkreath. News from Kynesgrove is fresh and terrifying
Economy: 25% price increase on all consumables (potions, food, arrows)
Social: A terrified hunter bursts into Dead Man's Drink: "The stones are glowing at Bleak Falls Barrow! I saw them... the dead... they're walking on the path up the mountain!"
Authority Response: Nenya pays the party for solving the vampire problem but is overshadowed by greater terror: "You've saved these people, but I fear you've only saved them for a worse fate."
Travel to Solitude:
Roads clogged with nervous refugees from near Kynesgrove
Distant Draugr patrols visible on ridges, standing silent and watchful
Every inn buzzing with terrified rumors confirming dragons have returned
Sessions 2-8: Settling Into the New Normal
World State:
Travel advisories issued by all Jarls
25% price hike becomes standard everywhere
Civil War remains a cold war, but tensions rising
Nahkriin's agents secretly beginning sabotage operations (not yet visible as pattern)
Party deals with Torygg's assassination and Act II chaos
Random Encounter Adjustments:
Increase frequency slightly
Mix of desperate refugees begging for food and newly-formed bandit gangs
First scattered reports of Draugr sightings near major Nordic ruins

