GM Tools & Reminders
Portraying World Decay
Rumors: NPCs share increasingly dire news at inns and markets
Visual Cues: Describe environmental changes (blighted lands, fortifications, refugees)
Economic: Track prices and availability strictlyΓÇöscarcity matters
Random Encounters: Adjust frequency and types to match current Tier
NPC Behavior: Show fear, paranoia, desperation in interactions
Investigation Adventures
When party investigates false flag attacks:
Evidence Inconsistencies: Wrong weapons for killing blows, illogical tracks, nothing stolen
Supernatural Clues: Unnatural cold, grave dust smell, rasping sounds on wind
Challenge: Proving evidence is fabricated without being accused as conspirators
Mechanical: Guile rolls to detect lies/truth are made with Disadvantage in Wraith-influenced areas
Heroic Intervention Tracking
When party kills a Dragon Priest:
Note which Priest and current session number
Add 2 sessions to next scheduled clock advancement
Narrate specific consequences: "News reaches you that the Draugr army at Fort Dunstad has fallen into disarray..."
Show players their actions matter through world state changes
Maintaining Tension
Never let players feel comfortable or safe
Economic pressure is constant (can they afford supplies?)
Every long rest in wilderness risks encounters
Cities offer relative safety but at cost (bribes, favors, quests)
Time mattersΓÇöworld degrades whether they act or not
Balancing Player Agency
Players can't stop everything (they'll feel the world decay)
Each Priest killed is specific disaster averted (they see impact)
Choices matter (which fire to put out first?)
Investigation and combat are equally valuable
Reward creative solutions to overwhelming problems

